HEADWORD: Unwonder
<hw>Un*won"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>wonder</ets>.]</ety> <def>To divest of the quality
of wonder or mystery; to interpret; to explain.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

